&lt;h2&gt;Vigeo Eiris and BNP Paribas&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created through a merger of two leading European agencies that specialised in rating companies and organisations on their environmental, social and governance (ESG) performance, Vigeo Eiris is a world-reputed extra-financial analysis agency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BNP Paribas has been taking part in the Vigeo Eiris (formerly Vigeo) ratings process since 2003. The Bank is required to fill out a questionnaire detailing its business and its corporate ESG policies. The questionnaire comprises six sections covering the six major domains which Vigeo Eiris sees as having major extra-financial impacts on a bank such as BNP Paribas, namely: Environment, Human Resources, Human Rights, Community Involvement, Business Behaviour and Corporate Governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table style="width: 100%;"&gt;
    &lt;tbody&gt;
        &lt;tr&gt;
            &lt;td style="width: 31.4229%; vertical-align: top;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
